The gradient is a vector composed of all of the partial derivatives of a function, calculated with respect to each input variable.\nabla f(x,y,z) =
\begin{bmatrix}
\frac{\partial}{\partial x}f(x,y,z) \\
\frac{\partial}{\partial y}f(x,y,z) \\
\frac{\partial}{\partial z}f(x,y,z)
\end{bmatrix} =
\begin{bmatrix}
\frac{\partial}{\partial x} \\
\frac{\partial}{\partial y} \\
\frac{\partial}{\partial z}
\end{bmatrix}
f(x,y,z) =
\begin{bmatrix}
9x^2z \\
-2y + 2z \\
3x^3 + 2y + 5
\end{bmatrix}

