print("Augmented matrix A =")
display(A_aug)
# Use sympy.rref() method
A_rref = A_aug.rref()

print("The Row echelon form of matrix A and the pivot columns : {}".format(A_rref))







The bottom row has all 0s. The set of vectors is linearly
dependent. The requirement for linear dependence is that you have more than just the trivial solution.

