For a given set of vectors, if the augmented matrix after performing row operations looks like an identity matrix, then the vectors are linearly independent i.e. a_1 = a_2 = a_3 = 0.

# create the augmented matrix
A_aug = Matrix([[1,0,2,0], [2,1,0,0], [1,1,1,0], [4,1,7,0]])
print("Augmented matrix A =")
